\b\i0 BRIEFING:\par
\b0\ldblquote It\rquote s not often I get such a good tip from idle gossip. \par
For weeks I heard rumours that the run-down southern town of Navenvolk was awash with fears of an imminent crisis. I didn\rquote t pay them much attention, until the \i Tribune\i0  confirmed that an evacuation had been announced \emdash  not an easy choice, considering they built a new City Hall there just a few months ago, replete with garish d\'e9cor\'85 and the regional treasury.\par
Heh, what a move that was; meant as some initiative to \lquote revitalise the area\rquote . Since then, the borough has been beset by a flood of trendy nobility, trying to gobble up cheap urban real estate in a newly fashionable area. It\rquote s become a rat\rquote s nest of rich and poor. I overheard a family at The Docks moaning that they were forced out of their hole in the wall for a few stacks of silver.\par
Given its civic importance, the councilmen of Navenvolk have enlisted a mercenary force to defend the town once they clear out, under the command of the well-respected Captain Ricardo. I hear he\rquote s quite the hero. Has the mind of a real\'85 strategist. Well, I guess that means they\rquote re expecting a siege. I\rquote ll have to find out more myself; the details have not been forthcoming.\par
I\rquote d better get going. Navenvolk is at least two days travel, and I can\rquote t be the only rogue planning to make a killing from a town full of abandoned property\'85\rdblquote\par
